96
00:07:31,350 --> 00:07:32,919
I'm a disgusting man.

97
00:07:58,578 --> 00:07:59,712
Stop.

98
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,081
Don't come within a one-meter radius.

99
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,083
No personal conversation
or physical contact is allowed.

100
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:05,785
-Mr. Do.
-Wait.

101
00:08:05,918 --> 00:08:09,021
You haven't taken a day off
since your contract was renewed.

102
00:08:09,088 --> 00:08:10,122
This is great.

103
00:08:10,189 --> 00:08:13,426
Why don't you take a few days off?

104
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:15,428
That's too sudden.

105
00:08:17,997 --> 00:08:19,398
Is this because of yesterday?

106
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:25,304
-Do you think what you did is a mistake?
-It was not a mistake.

107
00:08:26,138 --> 00:08:27,306
It wasn't a mistake.

108
00:08:28,975 --> 00:08:30,877
In any case, please

109
00:08:33,312 --> 00:08:34,380
keep some distance from me.

110
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,132
Please explain why
I should keep a distance.

111
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:54,500
I'm not

112
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:58,371
as nice

113
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:02,308
as you think I am.

114
00:09:07,446 --> 00:09:08,581
I know.

115
00:09:08,915 --> 00:09:11,417
Without you, I can't even
recognize people's faces.

116
00:09:12,051 --> 00:09:13,953
I can't tell whether
they're smiling or crying either.

117
00:09:14,687 --> 00:09:16,122
I'm such a fool.

118
00:09:17,890 --> 00:09:19,025
But there's a reason

119
00:09:20,426 --> 00:09:21,494
why I should do this,

120
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,762
so please leave.

121
00:09:25,498 --> 00:09:27,099
If you're near me,

122
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:30,503
I don't know...

123
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:36,576
what crazy thing I might do.

124
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,748
So please...

125
00:10:00,967 --> 00:10:02,068
Can you

126
00:10:02,768 --> 00:10:04,537
go get a bucket for me?

127
00:10:05,905 --> 00:10:08,341
I need something to catch my tears in.

128
00:10:11,744 --> 00:10:13,279
Why are you doing this?

129
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:15,748
I haven't heard from him.

130
00:10:16,215 --> 00:10:18,117
I mean Mr. Chastity.

131
00:10:18,417 --> 00:10:22,121
I knew he was taking advantage of you.

132
00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:25,291
What is it that he suddenly
had to take care of at that hour?

133
00:10:25,591 --> 00:10:28,561
Is he a neat freak?

134
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,831
Is he spring-cleaning his house?

135
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:33,432
Or could it be

136
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:37,069
that I signed the contract

137
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:40,673
way too fast?

138
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:46,312
Let me jump into the Han River right now.

139
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,915
My gosh.

140
00:10:56,856 --> 00:10:59,492
Ms. Park, I found Mr. Gi.

141
00:11:04,263 --> 00:11:05,398
I'm leaving.

142
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:07,600
Before you go,

143
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:09,935
tell me why you wanted me to come here.

144
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:13,072
Try saying, "Damn it."

145
00:11:13,139 --> 00:11:15,041
You're supposed to teach me how to act.

146
00:11:15,107 --> 00:11:16,442
Why are you making a teenager swear?

147
00:11:16,509 --> 00:11:18,577
This is your workplace,

148
00:11:18,644 --> 00:11:22,415
and that happens to be your first line.

149
00:11:23,149 --> 00:11:24,150
Damn it.

150
00:11:24,216 --> 00:11:26,719
See? I can make you swear right away.

151
00:11:26,786 --> 00:11:29,488
Are you telling me to say
such a lousy line in this shabby theater?

152
00:11:29,622 --> 00:11:31,624
After all the help with the guy,

153
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:34,694
shouldn't you at least let me
star in a TV show or something?

154
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:37,863
This is how I teach people how to act.

155
00:11:37,963 --> 00:11:40,332
I humiliate the actor

156
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:43,536
into acting more expressively.
It's called "method acting."

157
00:11:43,636 --> 00:11:47,206
Never let go of
your dreams and hopes, kid.

158
00:11:55,481 --> 00:11:57,116
Damn it.

159
00:12:06,459 --> 00:12:08,294
Can I borrow some bait?

160
00:12:10,863 --> 00:12:12,732
Ms. Park Ok-sun?

161
00:12:13,165 --> 00:12:15,201
I'm going to change my name.

162
00:12:16,969 --> 00:12:18,938
Have you been following me?

163
00:12:20,506 --> 00:12:22,808
You still don't know me?

164
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,911
I had someone else follow you.

165
00:12:29,081 --> 00:12:30,649
I mean...

166
00:12:31,016 --> 00:12:32,518
"You should trust people."

167
00:12:33,419 --> 00:12:35,387
"Always love someone."

168
00:12:36,021 --> 00:12:37,690
After telling me those sweet words,

169
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:40,359
one after another,

170
00:12:40,659 --> 00:12:42,995
as soon as I signed the contract,

171
00:12:43,062 --> 00:12:44,663
I stopped hearing from you.

172
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:46,699
It's moving.

173
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,668
You mean your heart is moving away?

174
00:12:50,536 --> 00:12:51,637
I mean that.

175
00:12:53,005 --> 00:12:54,273
If it's moving,

176
00:12:54,340 --> 00:12:57,943
let me, Veronica Park, hold it still.

177
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:15,161
It looks fantastic.

178
00:13:26,071 --> 00:13:29,275
She's not someone you can easily forget.

179
00:13:33,779 --> 00:13:35,481
Why do you have to be so attractive

180
00:13:35,548 --> 00:13:37,449
and sway a guy's heart?

181
00:13:38,250 --> 00:13:39,485
Am I?

182
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:40,886
First of all,

183
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,888
I'd like to apologize.

184
00:13:42,955 --> 00:13:45,624
For not calling me?

185
00:13:45,791 --> 00:13:47,393
For what Min-ik did.

186
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:53,833
You found out about him and me?

187
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:57,069
If Min-ik has ever hurt you,

188
00:13:57,136 --> 00:13:58,704
please forgive him.

189
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,072
I'm sorry.

190
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:04,009
It's understandable
that you got the wrong idea,

191
00:14:04,076 --> 00:14:05,311
but Mr. Do and I don't have

192
00:14:05,377 --> 00:14:07,246
the relationship you think--

193
00:14:07,313 --> 00:14:08,914
I'm the one who should apologize.

194
00:14:10,449 --> 00:14:12,751
Listening to Min-ik talk about you,

195
00:14:13,686 --> 00:14:15,721
a lot of thoughts went through my mind.

196
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:18,490
It took me a while
to come to a conclusion.

197
00:14:18,724 --> 00:14:20,492
If it's a bad one,

198
00:14:21,427 --> 00:14:22,895
I refuse to hear it.

199
00:14:31,103 --> 00:14:35,541
My conclusion was
that I couldn't make any conclusion.

200
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:39,612
Two guys fighting over a woman,

201
00:14:39,678 --> 00:14:41,881
telling each other to give up on her.

202
00:14:41,947 --> 00:14:43,349
It just doesn't make sense.

203
00:14:44,516 --> 00:14:46,552
It's not our decision to make.

204
00:14:46,819 --> 00:14:48,487
It's yours.

205
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:52,224
If you choose Min-ik, I'll give up on you.

206
00:14:53,726 --> 00:14:55,494
If you choose me...

207
00:14:56,996 --> 00:14:59,431
If that's your decision,

208
00:14:59,498 --> 00:15:01,233
I'll make Min-ik give up by all means.

209
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:03,569
So just think about yourself

210
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:05,504
and follow your heart.

211
00:15:06,005 --> 00:15:07,139
In that case,

212
00:15:08,641 --> 00:15:09,742
I say...

213
00:15:10,776 --> 00:15:15,147
Which guy should I choose?

214
00:15:15,881 --> 00:15:18,584
You look nervous.

215
00:15:22,788 --> 00:15:24,056
I know

216
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:27,593
a surefire way
to find out what you really want

217
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:30,062
in a situation like this.

218
00:15:30,396 --> 00:15:32,031
What's that?

219
00:15:43,042 --> 00:15:44,176
No.

220
00:15:45,244 --> 00:15:48,948
I'll wait until you feel
more sure about this.

221
00:15:50,816 --> 00:15:54,586
I wonder what Mr. Do is up to right now.

222
00:15:57,890 --> 00:16:00,025
I think we should hold back

223
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,027
until you make up your mind.

224
00:16:02,094 --> 00:16:04,596
You can hold your pee, yawn, tears
all you want,

225
00:16:04,663 --> 00:16:06,665
but what kind of a guy holds back
from kissing a girl?

226
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:07,833
Especially when

227
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:11,170
my heart is burning

228
00:16:11,770 --> 00:16:13,672
like a fire.

229
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:22,915
I'll get some more firewood.

230
00:16:26,352 --> 00:16:27,186
Gosh.

231
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:30,689
Mr. Gi!

232
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:32,791
Stop right there!

233
00:16:48,507 --> 00:16:50,709
Were you covered in filth or something?

234
00:16:51,610 --> 00:16:53,512
You were in the shower
for more than two hours.

235
00:16:55,647 --> 00:16:57,683
I am

236
00:16:59,818 --> 00:17:02,154
-filth myself.
-What?

237
00:17:05,724 --> 00:17:07,393
Thank you, Mom,

238
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:11,196
for accepting a jerk like me as your son.

239
00:17:11,663 --> 00:17:14,833
For feeding me and raising me.

240
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:17,569
But it wasn't all in vain.

241
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:20,305
Now I'm being rewarded

242
00:17:20,773 --> 00:17:22,708
with your marriage.

243
00:17:24,610 --> 00:17:27,579
Have you received the exclusive contract
with Cinepark?

244
00:17:28,647 --> 00:17:29,748
Not yet.

245
00:17:29,915 --> 00:17:30,983
Not yet?

246
00:17:32,818 --> 00:17:35,788
Come to think of it,
I haven't heard from Ms. Park in days.

247
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:40,559
Is everything all right
between you and Veronica?

248
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,595
-The thing is...
-Listen.

249
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:46,532
Veronica is a girl after all.

250
00:17:46,865 --> 00:17:49,401
If you hurt her feelings, do something.

251
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:53,472
Meet her and try to make it up to her.

252
00:18:10,789 --> 00:18:14,793
I'll meet Veronica
and ask her how she really feels.

253
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:18,297
If she wants to start seeing me again,

254
00:18:18,730 --> 00:18:20,065
what's the problem?

255
00:18:21,366 --> 00:18:25,170
But if she doesn't want to...

256
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:29,508
All right. In that case,

257
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,312
I'll think about it again.

258
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,997
Why did Mom have to say that?

259
00:18:57,536 --> 00:18:59,371
Maybe it's good that he's keeping
his distance.

260
00:19:01,106 --> 00:19:02,508
If he really loved me,

261
00:19:04,042 --> 00:19:07,146
I'd feel too bad for lying to him.

262
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:12,251
Yes, it's a good thing.

263
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:28,934
Hello.

264
00:19:29,368 --> 00:19:32,037
When I asked you to pretend to be me,

265
00:19:32,237 --> 00:19:35,174
I hadn't really planned on this.

266
00:19:36,575 --> 00:19:38,977
But regardless,

267
00:19:39,611 --> 00:19:42,748
the two friends, Gi Dae-ju and Do Min-ik,

268
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:45,884
started competing for me.

269
00:19:45,951 --> 00:19:47,419
It's such an interesting love triangle.

270
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:49,521
Is the man you're seeing

271
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,590
Mr. Gi?

272
00:19:52,624 --> 00:19:54,793
Why did he tell me nothing was going on?

273
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,962
-What?
-Nothing.

274
00:19:57,596 --> 00:19:59,131
Ms. Park.

