00:38:21,999 --> 00:38:24,135
You and I should find it out.

556
00:38:24,335 --> 00:38:26,170
I'll find it out on my own.

557
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:28,406
You stay out of this.

558
00:38:28,506 --> 00:38:31,642
Also, a security company
will visit tomorrow,

559
00:38:32,677 --> 00:38:34,011
just so you know.

560
00:38:37,381 --> 00:38:39,684
Mr. Do!

561
00:38:44,855 --> 00:38:47,291
SURVEILLANCE CAMERAS IN USE

562
00:38:51,962 --> 00:38:54,065
He really sent them here in the end.

563
00:38:58,936 --> 00:39:01,405
Hi, Myeong-jeong. Has he come?

564
00:39:02,306 --> 00:39:03,641
How is he?

565
00:39:07,912 --> 00:39:10,348
The glow has disappeared from his face.

566
00:39:12,917 --> 00:39:14,418
He looks like he has no energy.

567
00:39:14,485 --> 00:39:17,154
His shoulders are drooping
all the way down to his belly button.

568
00:39:19,757 --> 00:39:22,993
He looks so weighed down
that he even looks shorter.

569
00:39:27,064 --> 00:39:28,866
I'm sorry,

570
00:39:28,999 --> 00:39:30,735
but can you make sure he eats?

571
00:39:31,135 --> 00:39:32,603
Go.

572
00:39:35,439 --> 00:39:36,674
Mr. Do.

573
00:39:37,074 --> 00:39:39,210
Gal-hee asked me to get lunch for you.

574
00:39:39,276 --> 00:39:40,611
Are you craving anything?

575
00:39:41,812 --> 00:39:42,947
No.

576
00:39:45,082 --> 00:39:46,283
I see.

577
00:39:50,454 --> 00:39:53,557
It seems like he'd rather starve.

578
00:39:55,359 --> 00:39:57,928
Hey, what does it even mean
not to crave anything?

579
00:39:57,995 --> 00:39:59,363
I thought

580
00:39:59,430 --> 00:40:01,966
everyone always craves something.

581
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:05,503
Kkanpunggi, jajangmyeon, tangsuyuk,

582
00:40:05,903 --> 00:40:07,905
ox blood soup, beef intestine soup,

583
00:40:08,606 --> 00:40:09,673
fermented skate...

584
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:12,209
Hello?

585
00:40:12,309 --> 00:40:13,811
From Eun Jeong-su's résumé
to his contract,

586
00:40:13,878 --> 00:40:15,846
I sent over everything that might help.

587
00:40:16,380 --> 00:40:17,848
Please find him as soon as you can.

588
00:40:20,351 --> 00:40:21,485
Okay.

589
00:40:24,288 --> 00:40:25,956
Why did Eun Jeong-su

590
00:40:28,459 --> 00:40:30,027
go to Ms. Jeong's house?

591
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:36,901
Check your e-mail.

592
00:40:37,468 --> 00:40:40,438
The file was a bit unstable,

593
00:40:40,671 --> 00:40:42,606
so I sent it to you by e-mail

594
00:40:42,673 --> 00:40:45,009
as soon as my laptop was fixed.

595
00:40:46,610 --> 00:40:47,711
The file.

596
00:40:51,515 --> 00:40:53,984
E-MAILS

597
00:40:57,054 --> 00:40:58,622
MAN MAY BE UNJUST TO YOU

598
00:40:59,990 --> 00:41:01,091
What?

599
00:41:01,592 --> 00:41:03,360
"Incentives for the second half."

600
00:41:03,427 --> 00:41:06,530
"A clear stream has no fish in it"?

601
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:11,469
What's all this?

602
00:41:12,703 --> 00:41:15,439
MAN MAY BE UNJUST TO YOU
BUT GOD IS ALWAYS JUST TO EVERYONE

603
00:41:20,211 --> 00:41:21,212
"Aromi"?

604
00:41:21,278 --> 00:41:22,580
AROMI

605
00:41:22,646 --> 00:41:24,849
"May 2004."

606
00:41:25,416 --> 00:41:27,618
"Aromi, 100 million won"?

607
00:41:28,519 --> 00:41:30,621
Who said it's worth 100 million won?

608
00:41:30,988 --> 00:41:33,157
This isn't a platinum arowana.

609
00:41:33,224 --> 00:41:34,425
It's a golden arowana.

610
00:41:34,825 --> 00:41:36,460
What on earth is going on?

611
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:39,063
If this means

612
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:42,900
the Aromi I'm thinking of...

613
00:41:44,869 --> 00:41:46,136
GI DAE-JU

614
00:41:46,203 --> 00:41:47,271
"Dae-ju"?

615
00:41:50,975 --> 00:41:54,211
Why is Dae-ju's name on this file?

616
00:41:59,216 --> 00:42:01,185
He said he knew nothing about the file.

617
00:42:21,438 --> 00:42:23,240
DIRECTOR GI DAE-JU

618
00:42:26,443 --> 00:42:28,746
All right. If he says he doesn't know,

619
00:42:29,713 --> 00:42:30,948
he doesn't know.

620
00:42:46,497 --> 00:42:47,565
Come in.

621
00:42:54,204 --> 00:42:55,339
Mr. Do.

622
00:42:55,573 --> 00:42:58,309
It's about next week's joint meeting
of the media teams.

623
00:43:00,277 --> 00:43:01,612
You're Ms. Lee, right?

624
00:43:02,346 --> 00:43:04,815
Yes. Gal-hee is on vacation,

625
00:43:04,882 --> 00:43:07,017
so I came over to ask you
about your schedule next week.

626
00:43:08,185 --> 00:43:09,286
Just a second, please.

627
00:43:13,023 --> 00:43:14,191
Well...

628
00:43:15,326 --> 00:43:16,460
MAN MAY BE UNJUST TO YOU

629
00:43:18,195 --> 00:43:19,496
Tuesday would be the best for me.

630
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,667
Okay. I'll update you on this.

631
00:43:24,401 --> 00:43:25,536
Ms. Lee.

632
00:43:26,070 --> 00:43:27,137
Yes?

633
00:43:27,638 --> 00:43:30,841
What's Dae-ju's schedule today?

634
00:43:31,842 --> 00:43:35,179
He has a meeting with the PR Team soon.

635
00:43:37,581 --> 00:43:38,549
CONCERT TICKET

636
00:43:38,616 --> 00:43:40,351
The concert is today.

637
00:43:45,189 --> 00:43:46,657
I didn't realize it's Wednesday already.

638
00:43:47,491 --> 00:43:49,627
You'd better hurry up and get ready.

639
00:43:50,127 --> 00:43:52,162
You don't want to get stuck
in the rush-hour traffic.

640
00:43:52,229 --> 00:43:53,864
Your secretary is away too.

641
00:43:55,532 --> 00:43:56,500
I will.

642
00:44:12,249 --> 00:44:15,452
Do you remember? I promised you

643
00:44:15,519 --> 00:44:17,688
I'd protect Dae-ju

644
00:44:18,489 --> 00:44:19,690
by all means.

645
00:44:22,860 --> 00:44:25,229
I didn't expect it to be so hard

646
00:44:25,663 --> 00:44:27,264
to keep that simple promise.

647
00:44:40,944 --> 00:44:42,112
Hello, Ms. Lee.

648
00:44:42,846 --> 00:44:46,283
Can you come to the drivers' waiting room

649
00:44:46,383 --> 00:44:48,719
a bit later?

650
00:44:49,219 --> 00:44:50,354
I'd like to

651
00:44:52,489 --> 00:44:54,725
introduce you to a group.

652
00:44:57,528 --> 00:45:00,130
I'm sorry but I'm meeting someone later.

653
00:45:00,497 --> 00:45:02,566
It's okay to come late at night.

654
00:45:02,633 --> 00:45:04,868
There will be some familiar faces,

655
00:45:04,935 --> 00:45:06,737
and I'm sure you'll like it.

656
00:45:10,841 --> 00:45:13,177
Okay. See you later.

657
00:45:28,559 --> 00:45:29,727
THE CENTER FOR PERFORMING ARTS

658
00:45:43,307 --> 00:45:44,541
All right.

659
00:45:46,510 --> 00:45:48,445
When Ms. Park comes,

660
00:45:51,415 --> 00:45:52,883
I'll suggest

661
00:45:54,017 --> 00:45:55,519
we go out.

662
00:46:10,634 --> 00:46:12,469
I hope Ms. Jeong is doing okay.

663
00:46:13,570 --> 00:46:15,205
Is the security system working well?

664
00:46:23,046 --> 00:46:25,249
This is the first time
someone has given me flowers.

665
00:46:27,651 --> 00:46:31,255
Those flowers must have withered by now.

666
00:46:50,674 --> 00:46:53,243
Why are you not going in?

667
00:46:54,511 --> 00:46:57,548
Why are you here again?
I didn't even call you.

668
00:46:59,016 --> 00:47:00,117
What?

669
00:47:00,584 --> 00:47:03,620
Are you scared
he'll want to go out with you?

670
00:47:05,989 --> 00:47:07,324
What are you talking about?

671
00:47:09,092 --> 00:47:11,128
If he wants to go out with me,

672
00:47:11,528 --> 00:47:14,531
I'll smile and answer,

673
00:47:14,898 --> 00:47:17,734
"Okay, Mr. Do.
I want to go out with you too."

674
00:47:19,937 --> 00:47:23,674
I lied to Mr. Do,
and I'm paying for it now.

675
00:47:25,642 --> 00:47:27,411
I'll do as Ms. Park says.

676
00:47:30,214 --> 00:47:31,315
I can do it.

677
00:47:31,915 --> 00:47:33,050
What if he

678
00:47:33,851 --> 00:47:35,385
doesn't want to go out with you?

679
00:47:41,959 --> 00:47:43,093
Don't say that.

680
00:47:44,795 --> 00:47:47,698
I'm not hoping for that to happen anymore.

681
00:47:48,999 --> 00:47:50,200
I'll be going now.

682
00:47:50,968 --> 00:47:53,136
I hate to keep my boss waiting.

683
00:48:10,921 --> 00:48:12,356
Don't get your hopes up.

684
00:48:14,124 --> 00:48:15,759
Don't get your hopes up.

685
00:48:18,028 --> 00:48:19,863
Don't you dare get your hopes up.

686
00:49:32,102 --> 00:49:37,240
There is a man who is extremely important
in Veronica Park's life.

687
00:49:37,474 --> 00:49:39,209
And he will be

688
00:49:39,810 --> 00:49:41,645
at today's preview.

689
00:49:42,245 --> 00:49:44,815
So I want you to make me look

690
00:49:45,015 --> 00:49:48,051
even more attractive than yesterday.

691
00:49:48,485 --> 00:49:51,989
I absolutely need to catch his eye

692
00:49:52,122 --> 00:49:55,625
and get a kiss from him, okay?

693
00:49:55,692 --> 00:49:56,994
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

694
00:50:09,206 --> 00:50:10,574
Look who's here.

695
00:50:10,974 --> 00:50:13,076
Hello, Ms. Park.

696
00:50:13,410 --> 00:50:14,611
I can't do this.

697
00:50:35,432 --> 00:50:39,736
Isn't the concert today?

698
00:50:40,170 --> 00:50:43,340
I hate her so much.

699
00:50:43,473 --> 00:50:47,444
Mr. Do was waiting for Veronica Park

700
00:50:47,744 --> 00:50:49,780
with a bouquet of flowers in his hand.

701
00:50:50,981 --> 00:50:53,717
And I hated him for that.

702
00:50:54,117 --> 00:50:57,788
I also hated Veronica Park
for taking him away from me.

703
00:50:58,522 --> 00:50:59,790
Do you realize

704
00:51:01,124 --> 00:51:05,595
that you're backbiting yourself?

705
00:51:07,197 --> 00:51:11,001
After all, aren't you the woman

706
00:51:11,268 --> 00:51:13,637
who took Mr. Do away from you?

707
00:51:17,774 --> 00:51:21,645
I don't understand anything anymore.

708
00:51:27,084 --> 00:51:29,086
Who am I?

709
00:51:29,786 --> 00:51:33,190
Who is the woman I hate so much?

710
00:51:36,426 --> 00:51:37,694
Do you see now

711
00:51:39,329 --> 00:51:42,599
why I called it a severe punishment?

712
00:51:47,504 --> 00:51:48,605
Yes.

713
00:51:50,807 --> 00:51:52,209
I'm sorry, Ms. Park.

714
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:55,245
I have to end this today.

715
00:51:57,948 --> 00:52:00,250
I'll either tell Mr. Do the truth
and lose him

716
00:52:02,853 --> 00:52:04,488
or end my life.

717
00:52:06,423 --> 00:52:08,358
Anyway, it has to end today.

718
00:52:08,425 --> 00:52:09,893
I can't go on like this.

719
00:52:10,427 --> 00:52:12,129
So please...

720
00:52:13,630 --> 00:52:17,167
So please let me tell him the truth.

721
00:52:22,272 --> 00:52:23,473
Okay.

722
00:52:26,576 --> 00:52:30,547
I think you've been punished enough.

723
00:52:31,114 --> 00:52:32,516
But you know what?

724
00:52:35,018 --> 00:52:36,520
There's a problem.

725
00:52:39,422 --> 00:52:43,360
Once you hear this,

726
00:52:44,394 --> 00:52:45,662
you'll beg me

727
00:52:46,429 --> 00:52:49,432
to let you continue.

728
00:52:55,372 --> 00:52:56,840
I'm sorry, Ms. Park.

729
00:52:56,907 --> 00:52:58,875
If you don't leave now, you'll be late.

730
00:53:07,584 --> 00:53:09,085
What is it?

731
00:53:10,620 --> 00:53:11,721
Let's go.

732
00:53:12,255 --> 00:53:16,593
Whichever you choose, you have to
go back to the concert hall anyway.

733
00:53:25,068 --> 00:53:28,071
This is an announcement
about the 7 p.m. concert.

734
00:53:28,505 --> 00:53:30,640
The concert will start shortly.

735
00:53:31,074 --> 00:53:35,178
As the entrance will be closed
once the concert starts...

736
00:53:35,779 --> 00:53:37,047
Is she running late?

737
00:53:47,991 --> 00:53:49,326
Can we go faster?

738
00:53:52,229 --> 00:53:54,064
What were you going to tell me?

739
00:53:54,998 --> 00:53:57,300
BOSS

740
00:53:58,068 --> 00:53:59,236
Take it.

741
00:54:00,036 --> 00:54:01,438
Tell me first.

742
00:54:01,605 --> 00:54:03,540
Take the call first.

743
00:54:20,657 --> 00:54:21,858
What's that noise?

744
00:54:22,692 --> 00:54:25,228
Hello? Ms. Park?

745
00:54:27,063 --> 00:54:28,231
Ms. Park?

746
00:54:32,469 --> 00:54:34,004
NEW MEMBER

747
00:54:34,170 --> 00:54:37,240
The new member must be Gal-hee, right?

748
00:54:38,141 --> 00:54:41,444
If Gal-hee joins the group,
should we change our slogan?

749
00:54:42,479 --> 00:54:44,848
But I like our slogan now.

750
00:54:44,914 --> 00:54:46,082
Me too.

751
00:54:46,149 --> 00:54:47,751
It is made up of letters from our names

752
00:54:47,851 --> 00:54:51,621
mixed together with the famous quote
by Henry Wadsworth Longfellow.

753
00:54:51,921 --> 00:54:54,224
It means "justice prevails in the end".

754
00:54:55,925 --> 00:54:57,827
I think we're ready.

755
00:54:58,161 --> 00:55:01,031
As always, let's shout our slogan
before we begin.

756
00:55:01,097 --> 00:55:02,966
-Yes, ma'am!
-Yes, ma'am!

757
00:55:03,033 --> 00:55:04,234
-Man!
-May!

758
00:55:04,301 --> 00:55:05,435
-Be!
-Unjust!

759
00:55:05,502 --> 00:55:06,803
-To!
-You!

760
00:55:06,870 --> 00:55:07,971
-But!
-God!

761
00:55:08,038 --> 00:55:09,072
-Is!
-Always!

762
00:55:09,139 --> 00:55:10,206
-Just!
-To!

763
00:55:10,273 --> 00:55:11,341
Everyone!

764
00:55:15,011 --> 00:55:17,781
EULDOGUK

765
00:55:21,584 --> 00:55:22,752
Thank you.

766
00:55:29,993 --> 00:55:32,329
BOSS

767
00:55:33,630 --> 00:55:34,731
Hello.

768
00:55:34,931 --> 00:55:36,800
Is this Ms. Park's number?

769
00:55:38,001 --> 00:55:40,103
She has yet another phone?

770
00:55:41,571 --> 00:55:42,672
Yes, it is.

771
00:55:43,139 --> 00:55:45,809
I was just talking to her on the phone

772
00:55:46,076 --> 00:55:47,911
and heard a strange noise.

773
00:55:48,144 --> 00:55:49,713
Well, the thing is,

774
00:55:49,779 --> 00:55:52,282
Ms. Park had a car accident.

775
00:55:53,183 --> 00:55:54,250
Pardon?

776
00:55:54,918 --> 00:55:56,119
What happened?

777
00:55:56,886 --> 00:55:58,188
Is she hurt a lot?

778
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:00,056
She was already running late,

779
00:56:00,123 --> 00:56:02,826
and her previous secretary
suddenly showed up.

780
00:56:02,892 --> 00:56:04,661
So they took the same car.

781
00:56:05,729 --> 00:56:06,863
Is her previous secretary's name

782
00:56:09,132 --> 00:56:12,335
Jeong Gal-hee by any chance?

783
00:56:12,936 --> 00:56:14,437
Yes, that's right.

784
00:56:34,124 --> 00:56:36,192
Where are they right now?

785
00:56:39,496 --> 00:56:42,132
They're both in Sangmo Hospital.

786
00:56:42,265 --> 00:56:44,901
Ms. Park hurt her neck and
was sent to the neurosurgery ward,

787
00:56:44,968 --> 00:56:48,138
and Ms. Jeong hurt her arm and
was sent to the orthopedics ward.

788
00:56:52,275 --> 00:56:53,676
I'll erase it from my memory

789
00:56:54,344 --> 00:56:56,379
if you want me to.

790
00:56:57,180 --> 00:56:59,682
So please stop feeling so bad.

791
00:57:02,886 --> 00:57:04,320
Yes, I like you.

792
00:57:05,188 --> 00:57:07,590
I like you so much that I forget

793
00:57:08,291 --> 00:57:09,859
what I'm doing.

794
00:57:14,330 --> 00:57:16,666
I was torn between

795
00:57:16,733 --> 00:57:18,835
neurosurgery and orthopedics.

796
00:57:19,469 --> 00:57:22,639
Stop thinking about
where your love is headed.

797
00:57:22,705 --> 00:57:26,743
Think about where your feelings
originally came from.

798
00:57:57,273 --> 00:57:59,108
-The patient...
-I think

799
00:57:59,175 --> 00:58:00,643
she went up to the rooftop.

800
00:58:01,644 --> 00:58:02,712
Thank you.

801
00:58:43,887 --> 00:58:45,121
Mr. Do.

802
00:58:49,692 --> 00:58:51,828
How did you know I was here?

803
00:59:41,844 --> 00:59:43,079
As I came running here, I realized

804
00:59:43,146 --> 00:59:46,816
why I started to have feelings for her
in the first place.

805
00:59:47,050 --> 00:59:49,452
It was because she reminded me of you.

806
00:59:49,586 --> 00:59:51,955
Mr. Do said he likes me.

807
00:59:52,021 --> 00:59:54,190
I guess this is my last time
to look like this.

808
00:59:54,324 --> 00:59:56,459
-These are peanuts.
-Right. Don't you like peanuts?

809
00:59:56,593 --> 00:59:57,694
Who are you?

810
00:59:57,760 --> 00:59:58,928
Mr. Do Min-ik!

811
00:59:59,095 --> 01:00:00,563
Why did you do this to me?

812
01:00:00,630 --> 01:00:01,998
Why did you do it?

813
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:04,267
Subtitle translation by Min-jin Kim

